Let $O$ denote the intersection of the medians of $\triangle ABC.$ Then $OM = \frac{2}{3} \cdot OG,$ where $G$ denotes the centroid of $\triangle ABC.$ Also notice that $OG = \frac{1}{3} OS$ because the medians of equilateral triangles are perpendicular to their respective sides.

